        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 11:10AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1109 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Plano, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minooka, Millbrook, Lake Holiday, Channahon, Bristol, Millington,
Morris, Elwood, Carbon Hill, Plano, Coal City, Lisbon, Diamond,
Plattville, Shorewood, Yorkville, Newark, Somonauk, Rockdale,
Manhattan, Mazon, Sheridan, Braidwood, Wilmington, and Sandwich.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
